<p>123. In the second communication, the Government provided information on three cases. 
For one case, the Working Group decided to apply the six-month rule at its eighty-ninth 
session, for another case the Working Group sent the information received to sources for 
validation. Concerning the third case, the Government informed the Working Group that 
the name of the victim does not correspond to any case included in the records of the 
National Truth and Reparation Commission or to the National Reparation and 
Reconciliation Board.  
