<p>464. The Working Group sent two cases under its urgent action procedure to the 
Government. The first case concerned <b>Abdullah Madjed Sayah Al Nuaimy</b>, arrested at 
King Fahd bridge, on the border between Saudi Arabia and Bahrain, by Saudi Arabian 
police officers in October 2008. According to the Working Group&#8217;s methods of work, the 
Government of Bahrain received a copy of the case. The second case concerned <b>Bilal Abu 
Haikal</b>, arrested at the Riyadh airport on 18 July 2009. 
